summary: JK Rowling has challenged the police to arrest her for mocking Scotland's new hate crime law. The law criminalizes "stirring up hatred" against transgender people. Police initially received complaints about a social media post by Rowling and considered investigating her. However, they have decided not to take any further action. He has said that she is entitled to her views and that the hate crime law should not be used to suppress free speech.
